adjectives.description: wrinkled (comparative more wrinkled, superlative most wrinkled)

entries.meaning: (of a surface) Uneven, with many furrows and prominent points, often in reference to the skin or hide of animals.
examples: Synonyms: bewrinkled, rugose, wrinkly; see also Thesaurus:wrinkled
As the ocean receded from the beach it left the sand appearing wrinkled.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of wrinkle
